    "manuscript_sentence": "In N = 500 independent simulations of an evolving protocell population, the division-regularity phase (Clock) preceded the pattern-stability phase (Map) in 482 of 482 runs where both phase transitions occurred (100 %; binomial test p = 8.01 \u00d7 10\u207b\u00b9\u2074\u2076). The mean Clock \u2192 Map delay was 243 \u00b1 2319 ticks (Wilcoxon signed-rank W = 116 403, p = 1.66 \u00d7 10\u207b\u2079\u2078). Populations that achieved stable patterns (S > 0.3, N = 482) outperformed disorganized populations (S < 0.1, N = 18) with Hedges' g = 9.41."
  },
